		<outline text="May 2021" created="Sat, 01 May 2021 16:14:25 GMT" name="may2021" type="calendarMonth">
			<outline text="May 31" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:38:08 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="31">
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XCFJ_gJj_YQ&quot;&gt;Daddy don't live in that New York City no more&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Mon, 31 May 2021 15:09:02 GMT" type="outline" urlvideo="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XCFJ_gJj_YQ"/>
				<outline text="A piece &lt;a href=&quot;https://bhc3.com/2009/01/16/before-there-was-twitter-there-was-dave-winers-instant-outliner/&quot;&gt;Hutch Carpenter wrote&lt;/a&gt; about the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2018/05/06/170728.html&quot;&gt;Instant Outliner&lt;/a&gt;. Very much a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/search?q=%22Narrate+Your+Work%22&quot;&gt;Narrate Your Work&lt;/a&gt; tool. A feature supported by both &quot;LO2&quot; and &quot;drummer&quot;, and I'm guessing no other outliner. If others do support I/O then we should interop! :boom:" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 15:57:46 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Drummer milestone" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:38:09 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I reached a milestone this week in my &quot;drummer&quot; work, I now have an Electron version of the app. It means that I can now start to use Drummer in my everyday work. " created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:38:15 GMT" image="http://scripting.com/images/2019/09/10/drummer.png"/>
					<outline text="Up till now, I've been able to use Drummer to test and document Drummer. A desktop app, with access to the local file system gives me a better tool for writing basically book-length docs. Drummer has a lot of functionality to document. " created="Mon, 31 May 2021 14:16:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I've been doing all my blogging and howto writing in the Concord outliner since April 2017. That's a fair amount of work to port. And I'm going slowly and making it better where ever I can. Four years is enough time to have an idea where there are possible improvements to make. " created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:39:39 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm writing this in Drummer. If you can read it, then you know this much is working. :smile:" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:40:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="As they say..." created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:41:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Still diggin!&lt;/i&gt;" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 13:41:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: Maybe I did it too carefully, it worked the first time. :-)" created="Mon, 31 May 2021 14:16:17 GMT"/>
